full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/18/2023 UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE Immigration and Naturalization Service 510 South Vermont Avenue Los Angeles 5, California PLEASE REFER TO THIS FILE NUMBER Inv/Nic M. MCG Genia LAUTURE January 29, 1963 4816 W. 21st Street Los Angeles, 16, California Dear Madam: Please call at the office listed below, at the time and place indicated, for an interview in connection with an official matter. It is important that you keep this appointment. If you are unable to do so, please notify us promptly, using the reverse side of this letter, and we will arrange another appointment. You should bring this letter with you and present it at the location indicated below. Very truly yours, Asst. DISTRICT DIRECTOR OFFICE AT: 510 South Vermont Avenue ROOM NO. 214 DATE AND HOUR between 8:30 A.M. and 3:00 P.M. Monday FLOOR NO. through Friday ASK FOR Mrs. Solder REASON FOR APPOINTMENT Interview BRING WITH YOU: This letter, passport abd all other entry documents. 3/19/63 EXT GRANTED TO 4/18/63 Fap. G-56 (11-1-56) GPO 982478
